Package: staggeredGMM
Title: GMM Estimation of Treatment Effects under Staggered Adoption
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rishabh", "Bijani", , "rishabhbijani@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Parush", "Arora", , "parush.arora@ashoka.edu.in", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Implements the generalized method of moments (GMM) estimator
    for cohort x time-specific average treatment effects (CATTs) under
    staggered treatment adoption developed in Arora and Bijani (2026),
    "Efficient Estimation of Treatment Effects under Staggered Adoption:
    GMM Approach", Ashoka University Economics Discussion Paper 163, and
    Arora and Bijani (2026), "Estimating Treatment Effects under Staggered
    Timing and Non-Spherical Errors", available at SSRN. Three models are
    provided: pooled Toeplitz, cohort-specific Toeplitz, or fully
    unrestricted within-cohort covariance. Optional baseline-covariate
    adjustment via outcome regression is supported for all three
    estimators.
